CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 21, 1959, pg. B3 reads: "Write Sorority Constitution - These young ladies are members of Alpha Beta Sigma, a newly organized junior sorority, and are writing their constitution under the supervision of their sponsor, Miss Elaine Peoples. Left to right, seated: Sylvia Ostine, secretary; Margaret Burrell, president, and Jewel Taylor, vice president.  Standing; Joyce Brown, treasurer; Gloria Brown, social chairman; Miss Peoples and Wuanetta Hunt-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Alpha Beta Sigma junior sorority members, left to right, seated: Sylvia Ostine, Margaret Burrell, and Jewel Taylor; standing: Joyce Brown, Gloria Brown, Elaine Peoples, sponsor; and Wuanetta Hunt, gathered around table writing the sorority's constitution, another version
